 :demo mode: /n./ 1. [Sun] The state of being {heads down} in order to finish
code in time for a {demo}, usually due yesterday. 2. A mode in which video
games sit by themselves running through a portion of the game, also known as
`attract mode'. Some serious {app}s have a demo mode they use as a screen
saver, or may go through a demo mode on startup (for example, the Microsoft
Windows opening screen -- which lets you impress your neighbors without
actually having to put up with {Microsloth Windows}).